    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-12-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="867"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d867">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Weitzel</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Weitzel refers to department’s November 30,<note n="1" xml:id="d867fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> and says he is informed by secretary of state for foreign
                    affairs that his Government has prepared full powers giving authority to
                    minister to sign arbitration agreement as suggested in department’s note of
                    October 20, but not as proposed in note of November 2. Says former is
                    interpreted to be acceptance of terms of minister’s memorandum of July 10,
                    limiting arbitration to two lines, neither of which is Anderson line.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
